The paper discusses spectrum management within the context of licensed shared access (LSA) regulatory framework, which is a topic related to networking and communication (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the technology implementations and performance evaluation of LSA, which are topics related to information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography and security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the need for dynamic LSA spectrum management, which is a topic related to control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper discusses the standardization landscape of LSA, which is a topic related to computer networks and communications (cs.COM).
